external_knowledge:
- 'voyagers' metaphorically represents users who have completed orders;
- 'navigated to the destination' refers to the completion of orders;
- 'ports of call' metaphorically means shipping addresses where orders are delivered;
- 'currency of their journey' metaphorically refers to the payment status of their orders;
- 'average cost of their expeditions' represents the average total cost of their completed orders.

- "adventurers" refers to the users who placed the orders;
- "precious jewels" metaphorically refers to the products ordered;
- "treasure value" is the total cost calculated by multiplying the product price by the quantity ordered;
- "journey's status" encompasses the order status, date, and payment status;
- "destination" refers to the shipping address.

sql:
SELECT payment_gateway, COUNT(order_id) AS total_orders, SUM(order_total) AS total_revenue
FROM orders
GROUP BY payment_gateway;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM cancellations 
WHERE reason = 'Out of Stock';

SELECT order_id, order_total
FROM orders
WHERE payment_status = 'Pending';

SELECT level, COUNT(user_id) AS total_users
FROM loyalty_programs
GROUP BY level;

SELECT DISTINCT category_name 
FROM categories 
ORDER BY category_name;
